<title>JAPAN: Satoh to buy back 400 mln yen worth of its shares.</title>
<headline>Satoh to buy back 400 mln yen worth of its shares.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-07-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Satoh &amp; Co Ltd said on Tuesday it would buy back up to 220,000 of its shares, or up to 400 million yen worth, in order to introduce a stock option scheme for its employees.</p>
<p>Stock options give holders the right to buy shares at a set price within a certain period.</p>
<p>Earlier in May, Japan changed its law to allow firms to buy back up to 10 percent of their own shares for use in stock option schemes for employees and executives.</p>
<p>Japanese business leaders have said that the scheme would motivate employees to work harder.</p>
